{"pageProps":{"title":"Automaton Configuration","docs":{"handwritten":[{"replace":"config","src":"config.md","frontmatter":{},"sections":[{"stub":"automaton-config","title":"Automaton Config","level":1,"content":"<p>The <code>config</code> object can be imported from @quinscape/automaton-js and encapsulates the static / global context within an\nautomaton app.</p><pre><pre class=\"prism-code language-js p-3\" style=\"color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa\"><div class=\"token-line\" style=\"color:#393A34\"><span class=\"token keyword module\" style=\"color:#00009f\">import</span><span class=\"token plain\"> </span><span class=\"token imports punctuation\" style=\"color:#393A34\">{</span><span class=\"token imports\"> config </span><span class=\"token imports punctuation\" style=\"color:#393A34\">}</span><span class=\"token plain\"> </span><span class=\"token keyword module\" style=\"color:#00009f\">from</span><span class=\"token plain\"> </span><span class=\"token string\" style=\"color:#e3116c\">&quot;@quinscape/automaton-js&quot;</span><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"color:#393A34\">;</span></div></pre></pre><p>It supports a limited set of configuration properties which can be extended by the user for app-specific static / global\nconfiguration.</p>"},{"stub":"config-properties","title":"Config properties","level":2,"content":""},{"stub":"config.alternatestyles","title":"config.alternateStyles","level":3,"content":"<p>If the application uses alternate styles provided by the de.quinscape.automaton.runtime.provider.AlternateStyleProvider,\nthe information about these styles will be in <code>config.alternateStyles</code></p><p>This is mostly useful to write your own style-switcher as alternative to automaton&#x27;s &lt;StyleSwitcher/&gt; component</p><p>Example:</p><pre><pre class=\"prism-code language-json p-3\" style=\"color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa\"><div class=\"token-line\" style=\"color:#393A34\"><span class=\"token punctuation\" style=\"color